  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "ESsczbVpxN6YLb8vpaGTMwfTIC4=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:29.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "## Context\n\nAs of 2026-04-18, the core chat stack on Swarm is shipped and stable.\n\n## Shipped capabilities\n\n- **PSS 1-to-1 messaging** via `pss-messenger.ts` and `ChatManager.sendMessage`.\n- **Broadcast ping for new conversations** - `pss.subscribeAll` + `sendBroadcastPing`, with a synchronous `seenMessageIds` guard to deduplicate.\n- **Feed-indexed chat history** - paginated, ACT-encrypted, chapter-rotated. Both parties are grantees; a 64-byte wrapper chunk keeps ACT decode self-contained (`chat-history.ts`).\n- **Recovery across browser wipes** - `chatPeers[]` stored in the user manifest, with chapter tracking in localStorage using `Date.now()` to stay wipe-safe.\n- **Clear-all-chats** - two-step confirm in `conversation-list.tsx` calls `ph.swarm.clearChats()`, which bumps the chapter, wipes caches, and clears `chatPeers`.\n- **Dedup across Bee re-serves and broadcast+direct overlap** - `seenMessageIds` set, batch-trimmed.\n\n## Implications\n\nMessaging is no longer the bottleneck. Further chat investment should concentrate on live collaboration and polish items, not on the base conversation layer.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:29.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:29.000Z"
    }
  },
